title.rendered: NEWTECONS’ REPRESENTATIVE TOOK PART IN SCORING THE GRADUATION THESIS OF NATIONAL UNIVERSITY OF CIVIL ENGINEERING STUDENT

content.rendered:
[Hanoi, 12/06/2020] Mr. Tran Thanh Hai – Project Director of Newtecons has recently joined the graduation thesis grading committee of the National University of Civil Engineering. This is part of a training program series established by Newtecons to incubate and develop talents at key universities from the North to South of Vietnam.

The grading committee and K60XE students at the defence session

At the opening, Mr. Pham Thanh Tung – Dean of Construction Faculty delivered his best wishes to all K60XE students. This was an important milestone that determined the achievements of students after the whole education process. He hoped they would be confident to accomplish the project defence session.

Mr. Pham Thanh Tung – Dean of Construction Faculty spoke at the session

Mr. Tran Thanh Hai – Project Director of Newtecons, also a former student of the National University of Civil Engineering praised K60XE students for their successful completion of the defence session. They not only dedicated diligent efforts to the thesis, but also showcased a multi-dimensional critical thinking ability in English language, said Mr. Hai.

K60XE students at the graduation thesis defence session

By the end of the session, Newtecons had spotted potential candidates for the Company’s team.  It is hoped that Newtecons, by offering generous career opportunities in 2020, would be the next destination for young talents from prestigious universities across the country.
